# Claude Code Instructions for Zawaj Project

## Git Commit Policy

**CRITICAL RULE: NEVER commit changes unless explicitly instructed by the user.**

- Do NOT use `git commit` unless the user says "commit" or "commit these changes"
- Do NOT proactively commit after completing tasks
- Always wait for explicit user confirmation before committing
- Use `git status` and `git diff` to show changes, but don't commit them
- When in doubt, ASK before committing

## Exception
The only time to commit without asking is if the user explicitly says:
- "Commit this"
- "Commit these changes"
- "Create a commit"
- Similar direct instructions

## Always Remember
User approval is required before any git commit operation.

---

## Design System Components

When creating new screens or components for this app, use the following reusable components:

### Background
- **GradientBackground** (`Zawaj/Components/GradientBackground.swift`)
  - Use as the background for all screens
  - Place inside a `ZStack` as the first element
  ```swift
  var body: some View {
      ZStack {
          GradientBackground()
          // Content here
      }
  }
  ```

### Buttons
All buttons use iOS 26 Liquid Glass styles. Located in `Zawaj/Components/GlassButton.swift`:

- **GlassButton** - Standard action button (translucent glass style)
  ```swift
  GlassButton(title: "Continue") {
      // action
  }
  ```

- **GlassButtonPrimary** - Primary/prominent action button (opaque glass style)
  ```swift
  GlassButtonPrimary(title: "Submit") {
      // action
  }
  ```

- **GlassButtonDestructive** - Destructive action button (red, for deletions/sign out)
  ```swift
  GlassButtonDestructive(title: "Delete") {
      // action
  }
  ```

### Button Usage Guidelines
- Use `GlassButtonPrimary` for main call-to-action (submit, save, confirm)
- Use `GlassButton` for secondary actions (continue, cancel, skip)
- Use `GlassButtonDestructive` for destructive actions (delete, sign out)
- Apply `.disabled(!condition)` modifier for conditional enabling

## Screen Template

```swift
import SwiftUI

struct NewScreenView: View {
    var body: some View {
        ZStack {
            GradientBackground()

            VStack(spacing: 24) {
                // Content

                GlassButtonPrimary(title: "Primary Action") {
                    // action
                }
            }
            .padding(.horizontal, 24)
        }
    }
}

#Preview {
    ZStack {
        GradientBackground()
        NewScreenView()
    }
}
```

## Navigation
- Uses native SwiftUI `TabView` with iOS 26 glass styling
- Tab bar configured in `DashboardView.swift`
- Accent color: `Color(red: 0.94, green: 0.26, blue: 0.42)` (pink)

## Styling Conventions
- Card backgrounds: `.background(.regularMaterial, in: RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 16))`
- Text colors: `.foregroundColor(.white)` or `.foregroundColor(.white.opacity(0.7))`
- Horizontal padding: `.padding(.horizontal, 24)`
- Button height: 50pt
